{"parse":{"title":"Loxodromic navigation","pageid":48311098,"revid":798452837,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Loxodrome.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d6/Loxodrome.png/300px-Loxodrome.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d6/Loxodrome.png/450px-Loxodrome.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d6/Loxodrome.png/600px-Loxodrome.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"693\" data-file-height=\"694\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Loxodrome.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Rhumb line navigation path: &#946; = constant</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Loxodromic navigation</b> (from <a href=\"/wiki/Greek_language\" title=\"Greek language\">Greek</a> <i>\u03bb\u03bf\u03be\u00f3\u03c2</i>, oblique, and <i>\u03b4\u03c1\u00f3\u03bc\u03bf\u03c2</i>, path) is a method of navigation by following a <a href=\"/wiki/Rhumb_line\" title=\"Rhumb line\">rhumb line</a>, a curve on the surface of the <a href=\"/wiki/Earth_(planet)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Earth (planet)\">Earth</a> that follows the same angle at the intersection with each <a href=\"/wiki/Meridian_(geography)\" title=\"Meridian (geography)\">meridian</a>. This serves to maintain a steady course in sailing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WeintritNeumann2011_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-WeintritNeumann2011-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Navigating on a spherical surface with a fixed <a href=\"/wiki/Course_(navigation)\" title=\"Course (navigation)\">course</a> (<span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\beta }\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mi>&#x03B2;<!-- \u03b2 --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\beta }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7ed48a5e36207156fb792fa79d29925d2f7901e8\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.332ex; height:2.509ex;\" alt=\"\\beta \"/></span> in the figure) results in a spiral path that approaches the <a href=\"/wiki/North_Pole\" title=\"North Pole\">North Pole</a> for courses ranging from 270\u00ba to 090\u00ba and the <a href=\"/wiki/South_Pole\" title=\"South Pole\">South Pole</a> for courses from 090\u00ba to 270\u00ba. On a <a href=\"/wiki/Nautical_chart\" title=\"Nautical chart\">nautical chart</a> plotted according to the <a href=\"/wiki/Mercator_projection\" title=\"Mercator projection\">Mercator projection</a>, a loxodromic course appears as a straight line.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Comparison_Chart\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Comparison Chart</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Comparison_Chart\">Comparison Chart</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Loxodromic_navigation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Comparison Chart\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"center\"><div class=\"thumb tnone\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Orthodromic_vs_loxodromic.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Orthodromic_vs_loxodromic.png/400px-Orthodromic_vs_loxodromic.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Orthodromic_vs_loxodromic.png/600px-Orthodromic_vs_loxodromic.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Orthodromic_vs_loxodromic.png/800px-Orthodromic_vs_loxodromic.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1501\" data-file-height=\"1127\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Orthodromic_vs_loxodromic.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Comparison, of <a href=\"/wiki/Great_Circle\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Great Circle\">orthodromic</a> course (white) compared with a <a href=\"/wiki/Rhumb_line\" title=\"Rhumb line\">loxodromic</a> course (red).</div></div></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Loxodromic_navigation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Great_circle_navigation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Great circle navigation\">Great circle navigation</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Windrose_network\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Windrose network\">Windrose network</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Map\" title=\"Map\">Map</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Portolan_map\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Portolan map\">Portolan map</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Marine_sandglass\" title=\"Marine sandglass\">Marine sandglass</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Compass_rose\" title=\"Compass rose\">Compass rose</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Isoazimuthal\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Isoazimuthal\">Isoazimuthal</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Loxodromic_navigation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-WeintritNeumann2011-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-WeintritNeumann2011_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Adam Weintrit; Tomasz Neumann (7 June 2011). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.es/books?id=buMsPGyE7boC&amp;pg=PA139&amp;lpg=PA139&amp;dq=loxodromic+navigation&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=GIZeu8DBp5&amp;sig=1UcvzLLnZjKTSpaS9ECPnMmpidU&amp;hl=ca&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0CE4Q6AEwBWoVChMIq9ztmPzSyAIViXEUCh03eAKe#v=onepage&amp;q=loxodromic%20navigation&amp;f=false\"><i>Methods and Algorithms in Navigation: Marine Navigation and Safety of Sea Transportation</i></a>. CRC Press. pp.&#160;139\u2013. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-415-69114-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-415-69114-7\">978-0-415-69114-7</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rf